Vertex strongly tumid; pronotum wider, lateral margins strongly expanded and completely rounded in middle; elytral color much darker than head and pronotum (
Figs 57, 58
)

Elytra dark brown, each side with a yellowish spot subapically, spots nearly joining at elytral suture; tempora gradually narrowed behind eyes; elytra wider, ratio EL/EW 1.30; body length 6.4 mm; species from India (
Fig. 57
)

Elytra uniformly dark brown, without spots; tempora abruptly narrowed behind eyes; elytra narrower, ratio EL/EW more than 1.35; body longer than 7.0 mm; species from Tonkin (
